[h1 className:"font-lora" style:`{fontSize: 64, textAlign: "center"}`]THE COST OF INCREASING COSTS[/h1]

[p style:`{fontSize: 28, marginBottom: 32}`]Accounting for tuition increases at the 5Cs[/p]

by [Samson Zhang](https://tsl.news/author/samson-zhang/), [Rya Jetha](https://tsl.news/author/rya-jetha/), [Mariana Duran](https://tsl.news/author/mariana-duran/), [Reia Li](https://tsl.news/author/reia-li) and [Jenna McMurtry](https://tsl.news/author/jennamcmurtry/)

[Ava Francis-Hall](https://tsl.news/author/afrancisstudents-pitzer-edu/), [Julia Schwartz](https://tsl.news/author/juliaschwartz/) and [Katherine Tan](https://tsl.news/author/katherine-tan/) also contributed reporting

May 99, 2022

[/div]

Earlier this semester, Pomona College, Claremont McKenna College and Pitzer College announced plans to increase their respective tuition by 4.5 percent for the upcoming 2022-23 school year. Scripps College will follow suit with an increase to its tuition by 3.9 percent.

Since the 2013-14 school year, tuition has increased by more than 29 percent at each of the 5Cs, outpacing national, Los Angeles County and California inflation rates.

